Running:
    cd rabbitmq-server-3.0.0
    sudo make run

Everything should create the queues etc that it expects!
Can be set up manually using:

    ./plugins-src/rabbitmq-management/bin/rabbitmqadmin declare queue name=foo durable=true

    ./plugins-src/rabbitmq-management/bin/rabbitmqadmin declare exchange name=amp_exchange type=direct durable=true

    ./plugins-src/rabbitmq-management/bin/rabbitmqadmin declare binding source=amp_exchange destination_type=queue destination=foo routing_key=test


SSL stuff:

Overview:
    http://www.rabbitmq.com/ssl.html

More detail, discussing non-plain auth methods:
    http://www.rabbitmq.com/blog/2011/02/07/who-are-you-authentication-and-authorisation-in-rabbitmq-231/

Enabling EXTERNAL mechanism:
    http://hg.rabbitmq.com/rabbitmq-auth-mechanism-ssl/file/rabbitmq_v3_1_5/README

Validated user-id:
    http://www.rabbitmq.com/validated-user-id.html
